@@ -0,0 +1,278 @@
+# `@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus`
+
+The Reckoner — a kit-static petitioner registry and petition-scheduling
+helper API for Reckoner-gated writs. Petitioners declare their sources via
+the `petitioners` kit contribution; the Reckoner validates registrations at
+startup, applies priority defaults, and exposes the `petition()` /
+`withdraw()` ergonomic API for posting writs in `new` phase with
+`writ.ext['reckoner']` correctly populated.
+
+The CDC handler that watches held writs and decides whether to approve,
+defer, or decline them is a separate commission. This apparatus is the
+foundation: registry, types, configuration parsing, and the helpers.
+
+See also: [`docs/architecture/petitioner-registration.md`](../../../docs/architecture/petitioner-registration.md).
+
+---
+
+## Installation
+
+```sh
+pnpm add @shardworks/reckoner-apparatus
+```
+
+Register the apparatus in `guild.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "plugins": [
+    "@shardworks/clerk-apparatus",
+    "@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus"
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+## API
+
+```typescript
+interface ReckonerApi {
+  /**
+   * Post a writ in `new` phase with ext.reckoner set correctly.
+   * Validates source, applies priority defaults, validates dimensions,
+   * calls clerk.post(), then clerk.setWritExt().
+   */
+  petition(request: PetitionRequest): Promise<WritDoc>;
+
+  /**
+   * Withdraw a held writ by transitioning it to cancelled.
+   * Thin wrapper around clerk.transition(writId, 'cancelled', {resolution: reason}).
+   */
+  withdraw(writId: string, reason?: string): Promise<WritDoc>;
+
+  /** Snapshot of all registered petitioner descriptors (sealed at phase:started). */
+  petitioners(): ReadonlyArray<PetitionerDescriptor>;
+
+  /** Check whether a source id is in the registry. */
+  isRegistered(source: string): boolean;
+
+  /** Resolved Reckoner configuration with defaults applied. */
+  config(): ReckonerConfig;
+}
+```
+
+### Workflow 2 — `reckoner.petition()` (canonical path)
+
+```typescript
+const reckoner = guild().apparatus<ReckonerApi>('reckoner');
+
+const writ = await reckoner.petition({
+  // Writ fields (forwarded to clerk.post)
+  type:     'mandate',
+  title:    'Address vision drift detected at 04:00 UTC',
+  body:     '...',
+  codex:    'nexus',
+  parentId: 'w-...',       // optional
+
+  // Reckoner ext fields
+  source:     'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+  priority: {
+    visionRelation: 'vision-violator',
+    severity:       'serious',
+    scope:          'major-area',
+    time:           { decay: true, deadline: null },
+    domain:         ['quality'],
+  },
+  complexity: 'bounded',
+  payload:    { driftId: 'drift-42' },
+  labels:     { 'vision-keeper.io/vision-id': 'nexus' },
+});
+// writ.phase === 'new'
+// writ.ext['reckoner'] === { source, priority, complexity, payload, labels }
+```
+
+Omitted `priority` dimensions fall back to `defaultPriority()`:
+
+```typescript
+await reckoner.petition({
+  title: 'Minor quality issue',
+  body:  '...',
+  source: 'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+  priority: { visionRelation: 'vision-violator' },
+  // severity → 'minor', scope → 'minor-area', time → {decay:false,deadline:null}, domain → []
+});
+```
+
+### Workflow 1 — direct `clerk.post()` (always available)
+
+Any apparatus that has access to `clerk` can post a Reckoner-gated writ
+directly without depending on this apparatus:
+
+```typescript
+await clerk.post({
+  type:  'mandate',
+  title: '...',
+  body:  '...',
+  codex: 'nexus',
+});
+// Then set the ext slot via setWritExt() to mark it as Reckoner-gated.
+```
+
+The `petition()` helper is a convenience layer, not a gate.
+
+### Withdrawal
+
+```typescript
+await reckoner.withdraw(writId, 'Snapshot superseded by drift-43.');
+// Equivalent to clerk.transition(writId, 'cancelled', { resolution: '...' })
+```
+
+---
+
+## Priority dimensions
+
+Five independent axes that the Reckoner evaluates when scheduling:
+
+```typescript
+type Priority = {
+  visionRelation:
+    | 'vision-blocker'    // unreachable without this; future-blocking
+    | 'vision-violator'   // current state diverges from vision
+    | 'vision-advancer'   // pushes toward an aspirational aspect
+    | 'vision-neutral';   // doesn't touch the vision (default)
+
+  severity:
+    | 'critical'   // production breakage, security incident
+    | 'serious'    // significant ongoing degradation
+    | 'moderate'   // noticeable but tolerable
+    | 'minor';     // easy to live with (default)
+
+  scope:
+    | 'whole-product'  // every user / every commission
+    | 'major-area'     // a major feature or subsystem
+    | 'minor-area';    // a small slice (default)
+
+  time: {
+    decay:    boolean;         // worsens over time without intervention (default: false)
+    deadline: string | null;   // ISO date, or null (default: null)
+  };
+
+  domain: Array<DomainTag>;  // multi-valued classification tags (default: [])
+};
+```
+
+`DomainTag` values: `security`, `compliance`, `cost`, `feature`, `quality`,
+`infrastructure`, `documentation`, `research`, `ergonomics`.
+
+### `defaultPriority()`
+
+```typescript
+import { defaultPriority } from '@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus';
+
+defaultPriority();
+// {
+//   visionRelation: 'vision-neutral',
+//   severity:       'minor',
+//   scope:          'minor-area',
+//   time:           { decay: false, deadline: null },
+//   domain:         [],
+// }
+```
+
+---
+
+## Complexity
+
+Petitioner-side coarse estimate of expected agent token cost. Omit when
+there is no basis — omission is honest, guessing is misleading.
+
+```typescript
+type ComplexityTier =
+  | 'mechanical'    // ~50K–200K tokens
+  | 'bounded'       // ~200K–1M tokens
+  | 'exploratory'   // ~1M–5M tokens
+  | 'open-ended';   // ~5M+ tokens; multi-session
+```
+
+`complexity` is a peer field on `ext.reckoner`, not inside `Priority`.
+
+---
+
+## Configuration
+
+```json
+{
+  "reckoner": {
+    "enforceRegistration": false,
+    "disabledSources": []
+  }
+}
+```
+
+| Field | Type | Default | Description |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| `enforceRegistration` | `boolean` | `false` | When `true`, petitions from unregistered sources are declined (the `petition()` helper throws; the CDC handler cancels the writ). When `false`, a warning is logged and scheduling proceeds. |
+| `disabledSources` | `string[]` | `[]` | Sources skipped by the Reckoner — writs from these sources are left in `new` phase until the source is re-enabled. Enforced by the CDC handler, not by `petition()`. |
+
+---
+
+## Kit interface
+
+Plugins that want to post Reckoner-gated writs declare their sources via
+the `petitioners` kit contribution:
+
+```typescript
+// In the plugin's kit (or apparatus supportKit)
+export default {
+  kit: {
+    requires: ['reckoner'],
+    petitioners: [
+      {
+        source:      'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+        description: 'Periodic vision-vs-reality snapshots emitted when ' +
+                     'the keeper observes drift worth surfacing.',
+      },
+      {
+        source:      'vision-keeper.elaboration',
+        description: 'Elaboration proposals for advancing an underspecified vision.',
+      },
+    ],
+  },
+} satisfies Plugin;
+```
+
+### Source id grammar
+
+Source ids must follow the `{pluginId}.{kebab-suffix}` form — the
+contributing plugin's derived id, a literal `.`, then a kebab-case suffix
+(lowercase letters, digits, and single-hyphen separators; no leading or
+trailing hyphen). Mirrors Lattice trigger-types and Clerk link-kinds.
+
+Examples: `vision-keeper.snapshot`, `patron-bridge.commission`, `tech-debt.detected`.
+
+Malformed source ids and mismatched plugin-id prefixes are hard startup
+errors. Duplicate source ids across plugins are also a hard error.
+
+---
+
+## Exports
+
+| Export | Description |
+|---|---|
+| `createReckoner()` | Factory function that creates the apparatus plugin. |
+| `defaultPriority()` | Returns the Reckoner's default Priority object. |
+| `validateSourceId(id, opts?)` | Validate a source id string; throws on violations. |
+| `RECKONER_PLUGIN_ID` | The apparatus id constant (`'reckoner'`). |
+| `VALID_VISION_RELATION` | Allowed values for the `visionRelation` dimension. |
+| `VALID_SEVERITY` | Allowed values for the `severity` dimension. |
+| `VALID_SCOPE` | Allowed values for the `scope` dimension. |
+| `VALID_DOMAIN` | Allowed values for the `domain` tag. |
+| `type Priority` | The five-axis priority type. |
+| `type ComplexityTier` | The four-tier complexity type. |
+| `type ReckonerExt` | Shape of `writ.ext['reckoner']`. |
+| `type PetitionerDescriptor` | Kit contribution entry shape. |
+| `type PetitionRequest` | Input to `petition()`. |
+| `type ReckonerConfig` | Configuration shape (after defaults applied). |
+| `type ReckonerApi` | The apparatus runtime API. |
+| `type DomainTag` | Union of valid domain tag strings. |
